verbLexeme: 1. Of animals, birds and insects, to travel through the air by using wings. English = fly, wing.
2. Of animals, birds and insects, to move wings up and down. English = flap.
nominalLexeme: 1. The two parts of the body of some animals, insects and birds that are used for flying. English = wings.
2. In football or hockey, an attacking player who plays mainly on the far left or the far right of the pitch. English = winger.
